<TITLE> MM Ruhul Amin to be chief justice from June 1 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 25 (bdnews24.com)  Senior Appellate Division judge MM Ruhul Amin will take up his post as the next chief justice from June 1, an official at the president's office said Sunday. President Iajuddin Ahmed finalised his appointment as the 16th chief justice of Bangladesh, secretary to the president's office Sirajul Islam told bdnews24.com. MM Ruhul Amin is the second most senior judge of the Appellate Division. bdnews
